The photon sorting structure is a two-dimensional square array of subwavelength cylindrical cavities embedded in aluminum. Each unit cell contains two cavities of different radii and identical heights, arranged in a rhombic lattice, see Fig. 1. The individual cavities within the unit cell are designed to support an effective-cavity resonance or cavity mode (CM) with amplified EM fields, where the lowest-order mode’s frequency dependence is approximately given by [22]:Fig. 1
